    <h2 class="toRight"> The Statistics You <em>Need</em> To Know</h2>
    <p class="toRight moreTextSpacing">
      <ol class="moreTextSpacing">
        <li>In general, Blacks and Hispanics only represent 9.2% of the tech industry.</li>
        <li>In 2012, only 10% of all Computer Science degrees were held by Blacks, and 8% by Hispanics.</li>
        <li>In 2010, less than 1% of venture capital-backed company founders were Black</li>
        <li>In 2013, only 3% of the students who took the Advanced Placement test in Computer Science were Black. 8% were Hispanic.</li>
        <li>Of the 26% total women that made up the computer workforce in 2013, Black women only made up 3%, Asian women made up 5%, and Hispanic women made up 2% </li>
